  "text": "In order to well approximate the Hamming norm, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] let 0 < α < ǫ/ log(U ), where U is the largest item (in absolute values) in the stream(s). [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] considered that, if an estimator, sayd, approximates the truth, d, within a factor of 1 ± ǫ, thend α will be within (1 ± ǫ) α factor of d α . Our concern is, because α is very small, (1 ± ǫ) α ≈ 1 ± ǫα. If α = ǫ, then we will end up with a 1 ± ǫ 2 factor instead of the usual 1 ± ǫ factor we like to have.",
